Just to write down some explicit equations, let me explain how to find the

49:56.760 --> 50:01.560
SO3 rotation matrix corresponding to a matrix in SU2.

50:01.560 --> 50:05.720
Start by taking a position vector, r equals xyz,

50:05.720 --> 50:09.080
and convert it into the following two-by-two matrix,

50:09.080 --> 50:13.880
r dot the polymatrices, which is just x times the first polymatrix

