But they didn't know which mathematical objects it was based on.

57:43.080 --> 57:46.920
Rather than, say, platonic solids or triangles,

57:46.920 --> 57:50.280
the real building blocks of the universe are things like groups,

57:50.280 --> 57:54.280
vector spaces, you know, stuff like that.

57:56.920 --> 58:01.720
So it appears that nature is far more subtle and creative than we humans,

58:01.800 --> 58:05.960
because not only did she make these bizarre spin-one-half objects,

58:05.960 --> 58:09.480
she made a whole universe out of them.

58:10.840 --> 58:15.640
But strangely, even nature isn't free to do whatever she wants.

58:15.640 --> 58:22.360
She is constrained and constrained very severely by the laws of mathematics.

58:22.360 --> 58:28.600
That non-contractable path in s03 is simply there no matter what.

58:28.600 --> 58:32.520
So while nature could devise a spin-one-half particle,

58:32.520 --> 58:35.960
she could never devise, say, a spin-one-third particle,

58:35.960 --> 58:39.640
because the fundamental group of s03 is z mod 2

58:39.640 --> 58:44.200
and not z mod 3. So while nature is creative,

58:44.200 --> 58:47.800
that creativity can only exist within some very rigid

58:47.800 --> 58:53.000
and maybe even tautological bounds. So when we study physics and mathematics

58:53.000 --> 58:56.680
today, we still do, in the end, get that same

